f the Olympics.\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 211, \"end\": 214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\", \"score\": 0.9998634454000851, \"rank\": 0.00010337140964522063, \"text\": \"NRL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q10962\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\"}, {\"begin\": 221, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Johns\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matty Johns\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Johns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Johns\"}, {\"begin\": 256, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Stefanovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karl Stefanovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Stefanovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Stefanovic\"}, {\"begin\": 323, \"end\": 328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998328803, \"rank\": 1.672241947446222e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Johns and Aussie swimming legend James Magnussen have teamed up to deliver daily updates of the Olympic Games with their podcast Matty and the Missile in Paris.\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 402, \"end\": 417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Magnussen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"James Magnussen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Magnussen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Magnussen\"}, {\"begin\": 523, \"end\": 528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998328803, \"rank\": 1.672241947446222e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While recording their latest episode on Thursday night, the sporting legends got caught in a snap downpour of rain which drenched the French capital.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 665, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.979096346303207, \"rank\": 0.01959513885011311, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The commentators, who were joined by News Corp sports journalist Peter Badel, hilariously boasted about braving the storm as they sat in soaked shirts to continue the podcast.\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 719, \"end\": 728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999680593697349, \"rank\": 2.934450160334818e-05, \"text\": \"News Corp\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"score\": 0.9999999993965503, \"rank\": 3.6355833678761993e-10, \"text\": \"Peter\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The reason why we are soaked, as we got about seven or eight minutes in to the podcast and it absolutely started hammering down,\\\" Johns said.\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are in the middle of a storm, do not worry we hung in there as long as we could.\\\"\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Johns took a cheeky swipe at other media agencies, including Nine's Today show host Stefanovic who has been leading the broadcaster's coverage in Paris with co-presenter Sarah Abo.\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1236, \"end\": 1241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998328803, \"rank\": 1.672241947446222e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1260, \"end\": 1265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Jane_Smith\", \"score\": 0.676588089462496, \"rank\": 0.4067718740693402, \"text\": \"Sarah\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Jane_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Jane_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"(To) give an idea what we put up with, and why you should respect us so much, we saw CBS, NBC, Karl Stefanovic - they all just disappeared into the distance,\\\" Johns joked.\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1358, \"end\": 1361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS\", \"score\": 0.8516964201133057, \"rank\": 0.1217773462403416, \"text\": \"CBS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS\"}, {\"begin\": 1363, \"end\": 1366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9891772759668915, \"rank\": 0.005439791475151704, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We just hung in there as long as we could.\\\"\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1490, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Johns said despite the efforts of French soldiers attempting to usher them out of the rain, the podcast hosts were determined to \\\"stay the distance\\\".\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.979096346303207, \"rank\": 0.01959513885011311, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just want to do an apology, I am wearing a clear white shirt so my nipples are exposed,\\\" Johns laughed.\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You always wanted to be in a wet t-shirt competition did not you, Matty?\\\"\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Badel amusingly replied.\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 1850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been raining on and off in Paris since theOlympics Opening Ceremony last week, with hundreds of thousands of spectatorsbraving the wet to catch a glimpse of the proceedings.\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1886, \"end\": 1891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998328803, \"rank\": 1.672241947446222e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1910, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.5167697737229657, \"rank\": 0.7436172015619368, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Crowds of French locals, tourists and delegates lined the quays and banks of the River Seine under the overcast conditions to cheer on this year's Olympic athletes.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2044, \"end\": 2050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.979096346303207, \"rank\": 0.01959513885011311, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2115, \"end\": 2126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competitors were as thrilled as ever to compete at the international sporting event despite the trying conditions as they flowed down the river on boats.\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2353, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the six-kilometre parade along the Seine, athletes filed into grandstand-style seating next to the Eiffel Tower for the rest of the proceedings.\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2396, \"end\": 2401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999962285528, \"rank\": 3.771334412364834e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To join the conversation, pleaselog in.Do not have an account?Register  Join the conversation, you are commenting asLogout  Our Apps\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2639, \"entities\": []}]}"